Here are some tips for budget friendly trips:

âœˆï¸ *Avoid Peak Season* Not only a way to avoid crowds but youâ€™ll usually be able to get a better deal. You might not be able to guarantee nice weather, but your destination will at least be a lot less crowded!

âœˆï¸ *Book in Advance* Prices will often go up as time gets closer to your trip. Booking train journeys, accommodation & flights ahead of time guarantees you wonâ€™t get stung by a last minute expensive prices.

âœˆï¸ *Purchase travel insurance* It may seem like an additional upfront expense, but itâ€™s best to view it as an investment thatÂ can help you save money during medical emergencies and unexpected cancellations.

âœˆï¸ *Using public transportation* during your trip can save you money.Â The bus or whatever the local transport of the country youâ€™re visiting is always cheaperÂ than a taxi or an Uber. Walking is my personal favourite way to discover anywhere! 

âœˆï¸ *Choose cheaper accommodation* Hotels can be quite expensive so choose a more budget friendly stay such as a hostel or apartment. 

âœˆï¸ *Pack light* to avoid baggage expenses. Airports impose pretty hefty extra fees for large and heavy baggage. Also pack well, write lists (I have a notes app full of themğŸ˜„) so you donâ€™t forget anything and have to buy duplicate things abroad that you already have at home. 

âœˆï¸ *Eat Local* Stay away from the touristy areas. You can often see places that are popular with the locals, they serve cheaper food and youâ€™ll get a much more authentic look into the cuisine of that country!

âœˆï¸ *Save up frequent flyerÂ miles* Itâ€™s definitely worth joining a frequent flyer program & racking up those miles/points. Over time they really add up and can get you discounted flights and upgrades!

âœˆï¸ *Bring your own food*Â Whenever possible, stock up on sandwiches and snacks for the trip. Avoid buying meals at the airport/on the road/hotel minibar which are Â£Â£Â£.

âœˆï¸ *Skip overpriced Tours* Explore yourself, with the information available online, itâ€™s simple and easy to conduct your own tour for free rather than paying for a guide.

..and if you spend less on one adventure, you have money to spend on another! ğŸ¥³
